---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const APP_URL = 'https://dev-app.audioask.ai';
---

<Layout
  title="Transcribe any podcast in minutes — Audioask"
  description="Turn any podcast episode into a structured, timestamped, searchable transcript in just a few minutes. Speaker identification included."
  activePage="features"
  lang="en"
  alternatePath="/fonctionnalites/transcrire"
>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero dotbg">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 860px;">
    <div class="center" style="text-align: center;">
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="dot">●</span> Transcribe</div>
      <h1 style="margin-top: 18px;">Transcribe any podcast<br><span class="em-serif">in minutes.</span></h1>
      <p class="lede" style="margin: 20px auto 0; max-width: 54ch;">Turn any episode into a structured, timestamped, searchable text. Speaker identification included — read, search, share.</p>
      <div class="hero-ctas" style="justify-content: center; margin-top: 32px;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary lg" href={`${APP_URL}/signup`}>Try for free <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
        <span class="hero-meta-item"><span class="dotcheck">1h included · no card required</span></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
    <div class="eyebrow center"><span class="dot">●</span> How it works</div>
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 16px;">Three steps.<br><span class="serif-it">Thirty seconds of setup.</span></h2>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 24px; margin-top: 56px;">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <h3>Add</h3>
        <p>Search for any podcast channel or episode. Audioask pulls from a library of +185M episodes. Paste a URL if it's not listed yet.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <h3>Launch</h3>
        <p>Click "Transcribe". The AI gets to work. Count on about 3 minutes for a 1-hour episode — and you'll get a notification when it's ready.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <h3>Read</h3>
        <p>Your transcript is structured with timestamps and speakers. Read alongside the audio, search any word, or share the exact passage you need.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FEATURES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow center"><span class="dot">●</span> What you get</div>
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 16px;">Everything that makes<br><span class="serif-it">a good transcript.</span></h2>

    <div class="feat-grid" style="margin-top: 56px; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);">
      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-ico">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M12 2L12 12M5 7l7-5 7 5"/><path d="M5 7v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2V7"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>3 minutes per hour of audio</h3>
        <p>Our transcription pipeline is fast. A 2-hour episode is ready in under 6 minutes. No waiting overnight.</p>
        <div class="feat-visual" style="background: var(--cream-2);">
          <div style="position: absolute; inset: 24px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;">
            <div style="background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 12px 16px;">
              <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--accent-ink); margin-bottom: 8px;"><span>PROCESSING · 73%</span><span>1min 20s</span></div>
              <div style="height: 5px; background: var(--accent-tint); border-radius: 3px;"><div style="height: 100%; width: 73%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 3px;"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 8px;">
              <div style="padding: 10px 12px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
                <div style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 22px; color: var(--accent-ink);">~3 min</div>
                <div style="font-size: 10px; color: var(--ink-3);">per hour of audio</div>
              </div>
              <div style="padding: 10px 12px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; text-align: center;">
                <div style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 22px; color: var(--accent-ink);">99%+</div>
                <div style="font-size: 10px; color: var(--ink-3);">accuracy</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-ico">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="7"/><path d="M16 16l5 5"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Full-text search across all episodes</h3>
        <p>Every transcribed episode becomes searchable. Type a word, a topic, a name — Audioask jumps straight to the right passage with the exact timestamp.</p>
        <div class="feat-visual">
          <div style="position: absolute; inset: 20px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px;">
            <div style="background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 9px; padding: 8px 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 13px;">
              <span style="color: var(--ink-3);">⌕</span>
              <span>first principles</span>
              <span style="margin-left: auto; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; color: var(--accent-ink);">5 results</span>
            </div>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5px;">
              {["14:28", "38:50", "1:02:14"].map(ts => (
                <div style="background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 7px; padding: 7px 11px; display: flex; gap: 10px; font-size: 11px;">
                  <span style="font-family: var(--mono); color: var(--accent-ink); flex-shrink: 0;">{ts}</span>
                  <span style="color: var(--ink-2);">…the <span style="background: var(--accent-soft); padding: 0 3px; border-radius: 2px; color: var(--accent-ink);">first principles</span> approach…</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feat-card">
        <div class="feat-ico">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Community library: +185M episodes</h3>
        <p>When someone transcribes an episode, the whole community benefits. You often find a transcript already waiting — and pay zero credits for it.</p>
        <div class="feat-visual" style="background: var(--cream-2);">
          <div style="position: absolute; inset: 24px; text-align: center; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 8px;">
            <div style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 48px; line-height: 1; color: var(--accent-ink); letter-spacing: -0.03em;">+185M</div>
            <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink-3);">episodes available in the shared library</div>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; margin-top: 6px;">
              {["Acquired", "Lex Fridman", "Huberman Lab", "Founders", "TKP"].map(n => (
                <span style="padding: 2px 8px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 999px; font-size: 10.5px;">{n}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FOR WHO -->
<section class="section paper">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow center"><span class="dot">●</span> Who uses it</div>
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 16px;">Transcription for <span class="serif-it">every use case.</span></h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="who-card">
        <h4>Podcast enthusiasts</h4>
        <p>Never lose a great insight again. Read along, bookmark the best passages, and search back when you need them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <h4>Journalists &amp; researchers</h4>
        <p>Quote accurately, find sources in seconds. Your research library — fully searchable, always cited.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="who-card">
        <h4>Agencies &amp; teams</h4>
        <p>Produce summaries, newsletters, and content briefs from podcast content, hands-free. Automate the pipeline.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px;">
    <div class="eyebrow center"><span class="dot">●</span> FAQ</div>
    <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 16px;">Questions about<br><span class="serif-it">transcription.</span></h2>
    <div class="faq" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What languages are supported?</summary>
        <p>Audioask transcribes in French, English, Spanish, German, Italian, Portuguese, Dutch, and several other major languages. The detection is automatic — no need to specify it.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What does "1h of transcription included" mean?</summary>
        <p>The free plan includes 60 minutes of audio transcription per month. A 60-minute episode = 1 credit. A 30-minute episode = 0.5 credit. Unused minutes don't roll over.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Is the quality good enough for professional use?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Our engine (based on Whisper) achieves 99%+ accuracy on clean audio. In noisy conditions or with strong accents, expect minor errors. You can edit the transcript directly in the app.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I download the transcript?</summary>
        <p>Yes — on the Pro plan. You can export in TXT, Markdown, SRT (subtitles), and PDF formats. Free and Premium users can copy any passage directly from the app.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Can I transcribe private or unlisted episodes?</summary>
        <p>Yes — by pasting the audio URL directly. Any publicly accessible MP3/MP4 file can be transcribed.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section dark cta-final">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Try transcription <span class="em-serif">now.</span></h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin: 0 auto 36px; max-width: 48ch; color: var(--night-text-2);">1h of transcription included. No card required.</p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary lg" href={`${APP_URL}/signup`}>Create a free account <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.step-card { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px 24px; }
.step-num { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; color: var(--accent-ink); letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.step-card h3 { font-size: 18px; margin: 0 0 12px; }
.step-card p { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
.who-card { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px 24px; }
.who-card h4 { font-size: 16px; margin: 0 0 10px; }
.who-card p { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  [style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(3"] { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
}
</style>
</Layout>
